| INSERT INTO public."SectionText" (id, section, field_key, field_label, field_type, value, updated_at) VALUES ('8093d358-bc23-4f17-abdb-ff2dfcf7f264', 'footer', 'legal_privacy_content', 'Privacy Policy Content', 'textarea', 'Privacy Policy

Last updated: March 2026

Safe & Secure Services ("we," "us," or "our") respects your privacy. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, and protect your personal information when you visit our website or register for one of our training courses.
1. Information We Collect

    Contact information — name, email address, and phone number provided through our booking or contact forms.
    Course enrollment data — the course type, preferred date, and any special requests you submit.
    Usage data — standard server logs including IP address, browser type, and pages visited, collected automatically.

2. How We Use Your Information

    To confirm and manage course registrations.
    To respond to inquiries and provide customer support.
    To send course reminders and relevant safety training updates (you may opt out at any time).
    To comply with New Jersey state regulations applicable to safety and firearms training providers.

3. Data Sharing

We do not sell, rent, or trade your personal information. We may share data with third-party service providers (e.g., payment processors, email platforms) solely to operate our business, under strict confidentiality agreements. Where required by law or court order, we may disclose information to governmental authorities.
4. Data Retention

We retain enrollment records for as long as required to fulfill our legal obligations under NJ state firearms and safety training regulations, and for a minimum of three (3) years for general contact records.
5. Cookies

Our website may use essential cookies to maintain session state. We do not use advertising or cross-site tracking cookies. You may disable cookies in your browser settings; this will not affect your ability to view the site.
6. Your Rights

You have the right to request access to, correction of, or deletion of personal data we hold about you. To exercise these rights, contact us at info@sasstac.com.
7. Security

We implement industry-standard technical and organizational measures to protect your information from unauthorized access, loss, or disclosure.
8. Contact

For privacy-related questions, please contact us at info@sasstac.com or call (908) 758-4894.', '2026-07-13T09:24:03.809058+00:00');                                        |
