| INSERT INTO public."SectionText" (id, section, field_key, field_label, field_type, value, updated_at) VALUES ('b58f5848-a8fc-4335-9520-8ac0dfedc4cf', 'footer', 'legal_terms_content', 'Terms of Service Content', 'textarea', 'Terms of Service

Last updated: March 2026

These Terms of Service govern your use of the Safe & Secure Services website and your enrollment in any of our training courses. By accessing our site or registering for a course, you agree to these terms.
1. Eligibility

You must be at least 18 years of age (or the minimum age required by applicable NJ law for the specific course) to register for training. By enrolling, you confirm that you meet all legal eligibility requirements for the course type selected.
2. Course Registration & Payment

    Registration is confirmed upon receipt of full payment unless otherwise agreed in writing.
    Prices are listed in U.S. dollars and are subject to change without notice prior to registration.
    Group and corporate bookings are subject to a separate written agreement.

3. Cancellations & Rescheduling

    More than 7 days before the class: Full refund or free reschedule.
    3–7 days before the class: Course credit only; no cash refund.
    Less than 72 hours before the class: No refund or credit. Exceptions may be made for documented emergencies at our sole discretion.
    We reserve the right to cancel or reschedule a class due to insufficient enrollment or instructor unavailability. Registered students will receive a full refund or the option to reschedule at no additional charge.

4. Code of Conduct

All participants must behave in a safe, respectful, and lawful manner at all times. We reserve the right to remove any participant from a course for unsafe behavior, without refund.
5. Limitation of Liability

Safe & Secure Services is not liable for any indirect, incidental, or consequential damages arising from participation in our courses or use of our website. Our total liability shall not exceed the amount paid for the specific course in question.
6. Intellectual Property

All course materials, handouts, and website content are the exclusive property of Safe & Secure Services and may not be reproduced or distributed without prior written consent.
7. Governing Law

These Terms are governed by the laws of the State of New Jersey. Any disputes shall be resolved in the courts of Middlesex County, NJ.
8. Contact

Questions about these Terms? Email us at info@sasstac.com.', '2026-07-13T09:24:26.999625+00:00'); |
